# Site feedback — check every new session

At the **beginning of each conversation** on this project (before implementing unrelated requests), fetch and review live site feedback.

## Source (in order)

1. **Live JSON:** `https://windhamkiosk.netlify.app/feedback.json`
2. **Fallback:** `public/feedback.json` or `data/feedback.json` in the repo if the URL is unreachable
3. **Human view:** `https://windhamkiosk.netlify.app/feedback` for context

## What to do

- Parse `entries` (newest first by `createdAt`).
- Summarize **open, actionable** notes for the user (author, page/section, message).
- If the user’s task overlaps feedback, **implement or explicitly defer** those items; do not ignore relevant notes.
- If there is no new feedback since the last known state, say so briefly and continue.
- Do not run SQL or change production databases when acting on feedback — UI/content changes only unless the user asks otherwise.

## Entry shape

```json
{ "id", "author", "message", "page", "createdAt" }
```

## When to skip

Only skip if the user explicitly says “ignore feedback” or the session is purely informational with no site work.
